PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: categories for budgeting
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a color.

DATA: Transactions
MARKER: transactions
INTENT: financial transactions
---
The app holds a list of transactions. Each transaction has a category, an amount, a date, and a description.

STRUCTURE: Dashboard
MARKER: dashboard
INTENT: main screen for budget tracking
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a summary of total income and expenses, a list of categories with balances, and a add transaction button at the bottom.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user creates a new budget category
---
When the user taps the add category button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and selects a color. The new category appears in the list.

WHEN: Add Transaction
MARKER: add_transaction
INTENT: user records a new transaction
---
When the user taps the add transaction button, a form appears. The user selects a category, enters the amount, and adds a description. The new transaction appears in the list and updates the category balance.

ASSERT: Category Balance
MARKER: category_balance
INTENT: validation of category balance
---
A category's balance is the sum of all transactions in that category.

SURFACE: Labels and Buttons
MARKER: labels_buttons
INTENT: user interface elements
---
The add category button is labeled "New Category". The add transaction button is labeled "New Transaction". Error messages appear below forms if input is invalid.
---PART---

PART: __anchors
NAME:  Anchors
STATUS: draft

ANCHOR: User Ownership
MARKER: user_ownership
INTENT: rule for data ownership
---
All data belongs to the authenticated user. Sessions expire after 30 days of inactivity.